The paper deals with the performance analysis of MMSE MIMO receivers in the presence of channel correlations, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM). The use of the replica method, which is a statistical physics technique, suggests a possible connection to the field of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.MA). The analysis of large antenna numbers is also relevant to the field of networked systems (cs.NI) and signal processing (cs.SI).
